Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-only tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)] // MSTest v3+ with Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.OS
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    // Or use a runtime guard in older versions:
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
    // ...
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedFrame()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
    // ...
}
```

Or define a custom condition attribute (MSTest v3+):

```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public sealed class RequiresGpuAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
            return [new TestResult { Outcome = UnitTestOutcome.Inconclusive,
                                     TestFailureException = new AssertInconclusiveException("Requires local GPU") }];
        return base.Execute(testMethod);
    }
}

[RequiresGpu]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedFrame() { /* ... */ }
```

## 3. Retry flaky external API tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // MSTest v3.8+ — retries up to 3 times on failure
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var result = _weatherClient.GetForecast("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]`

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
}

[TestCleanup]
public void Cleanup()
{
    // Runs after EVERY test, regardless of pass/fail/exception
    if (_tempFile is not null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}

[TestMethod]
public void Export_WritesToDisk()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
    // Even if this throws, Cleanup still runs
    Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
}
```

---

**Summary of key MSTest mechanisms:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| Platform-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` or OS condition attributes |
| Skip in CI | Environment variable check + `Inconclusive` |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3.8+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs post-test) |

`Assert.Inconclusive` marks the test as "skipped" rather than failed — it won't break your build but will be visible in results.
